  "body": "<!-- **Are you in the right place?**\r\n1. For issues or feature requests, please create an issue in this repository.\r\n2. For general technical and non-technical questions, we are happy to help you on our [Rook.io Slack](https://Rook-io.slack.com).\r\n3. Did you already search the existing open issues for anything similar? -->\r\n\r\n**Is this a bug report or feature request?**\r\n* Bug Report\r\n\r\n**Deviation from expected behavior:**\r\n\r\n**Expected behavior:**\r\n\r\nIn the case of 11:2 ratio, we want 12345,123456. I.e. 2 SSDs needs to be split unequally.\r\nThe workaround is to exclude one of HDDs to make groups even.\r\n\r\n**How to reproduce it (minimal and precise):**\r\n<!-- Please let us know any circumstances for reproduction of your bug. -->\r\n\r\n11 HDDs and 2 SSDs can cause this:\r\n\r\n2019-01-25 21:42:00.871022 I | op-k8sutil: format and nodeName longer than 63 chars, nodeName nx16-edge101.nexenta.corp will be a42570cfc4cb86e81a4efebd39a0c004\r\nE0125 21:42:00.878365       1 runtime.go:66] Observed a panic: \"index out of range\" (runtime error: index out of range)\r\n/root/rook/src/github.com/rook/rook/vendor/k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/runtime/runtime.go:72\r\n/root/rook/src/github.com/rook/rook/vendor/k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/runtime/runtime.go:65\r\n/root/rook/src/github.com/rook/rook/vendor/k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/runtime/runtime.go:51\r\n/usr/local/go/src/runtime/asm_amd64.s:573\r\n/usr/local/go/src/runtime/panic.go:502\r\n/usr/local/go/src/runtime/panic.go:28\r\n/root/rook/src/github.com/rook/rook/pkg/operator/edgefs/cluster/target/layout.go:160\r\n/root/rook/src/github.com/rook/rook/pkg/operator/edgefs/cluster/utils.go:137\r\n/root/rook/src/github.com/rook/rook/pkg/operator/edgefs/cluster/cluster.go:106\r\n/root/rook/src/github.com/rook/rook/pkg/operator/edgefs/cluster/controller.go:154\r\n/root/rook/src/github.com/rook/rook/vendor/k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/wait/wait.go:331\r\n/root/rook/src/github.com/rook/rook/vendor/k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/wait/wait.go:227\r\n/root/rook/src/github.com/rook/rook/vendor/k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/wait/wait.go:221\r\n/root/rook/src/github.com/rook/rook/pkg/operator/edgefs/cluster/controller.go:148\r\n/root/rook/src/github.com/rook/rook/pkg/operator/edgefs/cluster/controller.go:100\r\n\r\n**Environment**:\r\n* OS (e.g. from /etc/os-release):\r\n* Kernel (e.g. `uname -a`):\r\n* Cloud provider or hardware configuration:\r\n* Rook version (use `rook version` inside of a Rook Pod):\r\n* Kubernetes version (use `kubectl version`):\r\n* Kubernetes cluster type (e.g. Tectonic, GKE, OpenShift):\r\n* Storage backend status (e.g. for Ceph use `ceph health` in the [Rook Ceph toolbox](https://rook.io/docs/Rook/master/toolbox.html)):\r\n",
